00:25:40.372 --> 00:25:41.840 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: I remember
this from school

00:25:41.840 --> 00:25:44.243 align:middle line:84%
>>BRADEN: This is the history
of the whole world forever.

00:25:44.243 --> 00:25:46.712 align:middle line:84%
Now, the problem
is new discoveries

00:25:46.712 --> 00:25:47.579 align:middle line:90%
have overturned this.

00:25:47.579 --> 00:25:51.450 align:middle line:84%
But they're not being shared in
the media and in the classroom.

00:25:51.450 --> 00:25:53.719 align:middle line:84%
And I've had the
opportunity personally

00:25:53.719 --> 00:25:55.421 align:middle line:90%
to explore some of these sites.

00:25:55.421 --> 00:25:56.588 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Wow.

00:25:56.588 --> 00:25:58.023 align:middle line:84%
>>BRADEN: These
are peer-reviewed,

00:25:58.023 --> 00:25:59.291 align:middle line:90%
scientifically accepted.

00:25:59.291 --> 00:26:01.093 align:middle line:84%
These isn't a
hypothesis or a theory

00:26:01.093 --> 00:26:02.327 align:middle line:90%
about Atlantis or Lemuria.

00:26:02.327 --> 00:26:05.264 align:middle line:84%
These are sites that are
scientifically documented

00:26:05.264 --> 00:26:06.031 align:middle line:90%
to be much older.

00:26:06.031 --> 00:26:07.433 align:middle line:84%
So I'm going to
give two examples.

00:26:07.433 --> 00:26:08.967 align:middle line:90%
One, I personally have explored.

00:26:08.967 --> 00:26:10.602 align:middle line:90%
This is northern Peru.

00:26:10.602 --> 00:26:14.640 align:middle line:84%
This site now is older than
any other advanced civilization

00:26:14.640 --> 00:26:16.141 align:middle line:90%
in all of the Americas.

00:26:16.141 --> 00:26:19.144 align:middle line:84%
Older than the Maya, than
the Aztec, than the Inca,

00:26:19.144 --> 00:26:19.978 align:middle line:90%
than the Olmec.

00:26:19.978 --> 00:26:22.981 align:middle line:84%
This is an area that
is called Caral, Peru.

00:26:22.981 --> 00:26:27.319 align:middle line:84%
Five pyramids, two massive,
massive central plazas

00:26:27.319 --> 00:26:29.588 align:middle line:84%
like the one you're seeing
on your screen right now--

00:26:29.588 --> 00:26:30.823 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Those have
all been discovered?

00:26:30.823 --> 00:26:31.523 align:middle line:90%
Wow.

00:26:31.523 --> 00:26:33.292 align:middle line:84%
>>BRADEN: This is an
ongoing archaeological site.

00:26:33.292 --> 00:26:33.525 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: --archaeological--

00:26:33.525 --> 00:26:35.194 align:middle line:84%
>>BRADEN: It's an
active site right now.

00:26:35.194 --> 00:26:40.032 align:middle line:84%
I was there the day that
the labs returned the dates

00:26:40.032 --> 00:26:42.334 align:middle line:84%
for the dating for this,
the independent labs.

00:26:42.334 --> 00:26:44.470 align:middle line:84%
The bottom line is that
this site collapsed

00:26:44.470 --> 00:26:46.438 align:middle line:84%
when we're told that
civilization began.

00:26:46.438 --> 00:26:49.208 align:middle line:84%
This site is dated between
5,000 and 7,000 years--

00:26:49.208 --> 00:26:50.175 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: So it existed--

00:26:50.175 --> 00:26:51.109 align:middle line:84%
>>BRADEN: --is an
advanced civilization.

00:26:51.109 --> 00:26:53.145 align:middle line:84%
When we're told that
civilization began--

00:26:53.145 --> 00:26:53.512 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: --began here--

00:26:53.512 --> 00:26:55.581 align:middle line:84%
>>BRADEN: This is just--
this is one example.

00:26:55.581 --> 00:26:57.249 align:middle line:90%
Let's cut to the chase.

00:26:57.249 --> 00:27:00.219 align:middle line:84%
The oldest civilization now
scientifically documented

00:27:00.219 --> 00:27:02.788 align:middle line:84%
anywhere in the
world right now is

00:27:02.788 --> 00:27:04.490 align:middle line:84%
a site that's
called Gobekli Tepe.

00:27:04.490 --> 00:27:05.190 align:middle line:90%
It's in Turkey.

00:27:05.190 --> 00:27:06.592 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And you
went there for us.

00:27:06.592 --> 00:27:07.092 align:middle line:90%
Wow.

00:27:07.092 --> 00:27:08.627 align:middle line:84%
>>BRADEN: This is
an amazing site.

00:27:08.627 --> 00:27:09.628 align:middle line:90%
It's an active site.

00:27:09.628 --> 00:27:11.763 align:middle line:84%
