these dates, there's

00:27:58.010 --> 00:27:59.077 align:middle line:90%
a new story that develops.

00:27:59.077 --> 00:28:01.613 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: But why isn't
this more talked about?

00:28:01.613 --> 00:28:03.448 align:middle line:90%
Why isn't this discovery--

00:28:03.448 --> 00:28:04.816 align:middle line:84%
>>BRADEN: You
know, Lisa, I think

00:28:04.816 --> 00:28:07.619 align:middle line:84%
it takes time for
new discoveries

00:28:07.619 --> 00:28:11.523 align:middle line:90%
to trickle down into mainstream.

00:28:11.523 --> 00:28:12.824 align:middle line:90%
There's a lot of money involved.

00:28:12.824 --> 00:28:17.462 align:middle line:84%
For 150 years there's a
scientific story of us,

00:28:17.462 --> 00:28:19.231 align:middle line:84%
our relationship to
the Earth, and our past

00:28:19.231 --> 00:28:20.032 align:middle line:90%
that's been taught.

00:28:20.032 --> 00:28:21.366 align:middle line:90%
It takes time to change that.

